monty in withnail and i ken russell and françois truffaut contents  early life  film career  author  personal life  filmography  acting  directing  screenwriting  bibliography  references  external links early lifeedit bruce robinson was born in london he grew up in broadstairs kent where he attended the charles dickens secondary modern school his parents were mabel robinson and american lawyer carl casriel who had a shortterm relationship during world war ii his father was a lithuanian jew as a child robinson was constantly brutally abused by his stepfather rob an ex raf navigator and a wholesale newsagent who knew the boy wasnt his son he had an elder sister elly whom he asked to teach him some french film careeredit robinson at the premiere of the rum diary in his youth robinson aspired to be an actor and was admitted to the central school of speech and drama in london his first film role was as benvolio in franco zeffirellis film adaptation of romeo and juliet  he then appeared in ken russells the music lovers  barney plattsmillss private road  and françois truffauts the story of adele h  after spending several years out of work and living on social security payments he became disenchanted and began writing screenplays he was soon commissioned by david puttnam to write the screenplay for roland joffés the killing fields  robinson was nominated for an academy award and won a bafta for his work in  robinson wrote again for joffé on fat man and little boy he returned to acting briefly in  taking a role in the film still crazy he is perhaps best known as the creative force behind the loosely autobiographical film withnail and i  which he based on his time as a struggling outofwork actor the character withnail is reportedly based on his friend vivian mackerrell the character i marwood on himself though unsuccessful at the box office because of its success on video it has since been described as one of britains biggest cult films the film also launched the acting career of richard e grant robinsons next two outings as a director how to get ahead in advertising teaming him again with richard e grant and jennifer  a hollywood thriller were not as well received robinson became disillusioned with the restrictive filmmaking practices of hollywood and stopped directing to concentrate solely on writing he wrote the screenplays for the films return to paradise  and in dreams  but both were altered drastically by their producers leaving robinson once again disappointed robinson eventually returned to directing with an adaptation of hunter s thompsons novel the rum diary with the main role performed by johnny depp with aaron eckhart and richard jenkins also on board filming started on  march  in puerto rico it was released in  in  robinsons comic novella paranoia in the launderette was substantially filled out and adapted for the screen as a fantastic fear of everything starring simon pegg robinson has completed a screenplay for his novel the peculiar memories of thomas penman and a book on jack the ripper titled they all love jack in which he names the real culprit as michael maybrick otherwise best known as a composer of songs such as the holy city and brother of another ripper suspect james maybrick authoredit robinson is also a successful author his first published work was the semiautobiographical novel the peculiar memories of thomas penman in  based on his own childhood growing up in broadstairs kent in  smoking in bed conversations with bruce robinson edited by alistair owen was published made up of a selection of interviews given by robinson meanwhile since becoming a father robinson has also written two childrens books the obvious elephant  and harold and the duck  both illustrated by his wife the former is also available as an audiobook edition  read by lorelei king and michael maloney he spent about  years collecting and researching the materials on the mystery of jack the ripper which later became his book they all love jack busting the ripper  personal lifeedit robinson currently lives in herefordshire with his wife the artist sophie windham he has two children lily and willoughby christian b  robinson is a recovering alcoholic having stopped drinking in  he relapsed before and during the filming of the rum diary but stopped drinking again after the film was finished filmographyedit actingedit romeo and juliet  the other people  the music lovers  tamlin  private road  los viajes escolares  the story of adele h  kleinhoff hotel  the brute  still crazy  directingedit withnail and i  how to get ahead in advertising  jennifer   the rum diary  screenwritingedit the killing fields  withnail and i  how to get ahead in advertising  fat man and little boy  jennifer   return to paradise  in dreams  the rum diary  bibliographyedit paranoia in the launderette  the peculiar memories of thomas penman  the obvious elephant  harold and the duck  they all love jack busting the ripper  referencesedit  interview by robert chalmers  february  the independent on sunday the new review p  february  independentcouk retrieved  february    httpwwwtelegraphcouknewsuknewscrimejacktherippermysterysolvedhtml  jack the ripper has bruce robinson solved the worlds most famous crime the telegraph retrieved  october    how one man revealed jack the rippers identity the full story gq retrieved  october    bfi screenonline withnail and i  screenonlineorguk retrieved  february    russell jamie films article article – how withnail  i became a cult bbc retrieved  february    bfi screenonline robinson bruce – biography screenonlineorguk  may  retrieved  february    bruce robinson  britmovie  home of british films britmovie retrieved  february    withnails bruce robinson to direct the rum diary  movie news  empire empireonlinecom  december  retrieved  february    the rum diary now filming ign  april  retrieved  august    chalmers robert  february  bruce robinson i started drinking again because of the rum diary the independent retrieved  february   external linksedit wikiquote has quotations related to bruce robinson bruce robinson on imdb bruce robinson biography and credits at the british film institutes screenonline httpwwwchannelcomcarftfeaturefeature httpwwwtelegraphcouknewsuknewscrimejacktherippermysterysolvedhtml v t e films directed by bruce robinson withnail and i  how to get ahead in advertising  jennifer   the rum diary  v t e bafta award for best adapted screenplay ruth prawer jhabvala  bruce robinson  richard condon and janet roach  kurt luedtke  claude berri and gérard brach  jeanclaude carrière and philip kaufman  christopher hampton  nicholas pileggi and martin scorsese  dick clement roddy doyle and ian la frenais  michael tolkin  steven zaillian  paul attanasio  john hodge  anthony minghella  baz luhrmann and craig pearce  elaine may  neil jordan  stephen gaghan  ted elliott terry rossio roger s h schulman and joe stillman  charlie kaufman and donald kaufman  philippa boyens peter jackson and fran walsh  alexander payne and jim taylor  larry mcmurtry and diana ossana  jeremy brock and peter morgan  ronald harwood  simon beaufoy  jason reitman and sheldon turner  aaron sorkin  bridget oconnor and peter straughan  david o russell  steve coogan and jeff pope  anthony mccarten  adam mckay and charles randolph  luke davies  v t e writers guild of america award for best adapted screenplay adapted drama – retired waldo salt  robert anderson  ernest tidyman  francis ford coppola and mario puzo  waldo salt and norman wexler  francis ford coppola and mario puzo  bo goldman and lawrence hauben  william goldman  denne bart petitclerc  oliver stone  robert benton  alvin sargent  ernest thompson  costagavras and donald e stewart  julius j epstein  adapted comedy – retired arnold schulman  ring lardner jr  john paxton  jay presson allen  alvin sargent  lionel chetwynd and mordecai richler  neil simon  blake edwards and frank waldman  larry gelbart  elaine may and warren beatty  bernard slade  jerzy kosiński  jim abrahams david zucker and jerry zucker  gerard ayres  blake edwards  james l brooks  adapted screenplay –present bruce robinson  richard condon and janet roach  ruth prawer jhabvala  steve martin  christopher hampton  alfred uhry  michael blake  ted tally  michael tolkin  steven zaillian  eric roth  emma thompson  billy bob thornton  curtis hanson and brian helgeland  scott frank  alexander payne and jim taylor  stephen gaghan  akiva goldsman  david hare  shari springer berman and robert pulcini  alexander payne and jim taylor  larry mcmurtry and diana ossana  william monahan  joel coen and ethan coen  simon beaufoy  jason reitman and sheldon turner  aaron sorkin  alexander payne jim rash and nat faxon  chris terrio  billy ray  graham moore  adam mckay and charles randolph  eric heisserer  authority control worldcat identities viaf  lccn no isni     gnd  sudoc  bnf cb data bne xx retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlebrucerobinsonoldid categories bafta winners peoplewriters guild of america award winnersenglish film directorsenglish screenwritersalumni of the central school of speech and dramapeople from broadstairs birthsliving peoplehidden categories engvarb from august use dmy dates from august articles with hcardswikipedia articles with viaf identifierswikipedia articles with lccn identifierswikipedia articles with isni identifierswikipedia articles with gnd identifierswikipedia articles with bnf identifiers navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikipediacommunity portalrecent changescontact page tools what links hererelated changesupload filespecial pagespermanent linkpage informationwikidata itemcite this page printexport create a bookdownload as pdfprintable version in other proj