 from  until march  when upon  his recommendation robert willett was promoted to fill that role he has served as a director since   as ceo of cognex dr shillman gained international recognition for his unique work hardplay hard management style he was named inc magazines entrepreneur of the year in  received an achievement award in leadership from the automated imaging association in  and received the north american semi award in  for his contributions to the semiconductor industry dr shillman holds a bsee from northeastern university as well as an msee and a phd from the massachusetts institute of technology patrick a alias senior vice president cognex corporationmr alias has been senior vice president of cognex since april  and previously was executive vice president of sales and marketing at cognex from  through april  prior to joining cognex mr alias spent more than  years in high technology management in europe japan and the united states he holds master’s degrees in electronics mathematics and economics and is a graduate of the advanced management program of the harvard business school mr alias was first elected a director of cognex in  eugene banucci founder and former chairman and chief executive officer atmi incdr banucci is the founder and former chairman and chief executive officer of atmi inc a publicly held company that was acquired in  prior to starting atmi he held management positions at general electric company and american cyanamid company dr banucci has served on numerous boards in particular he was a member of the board of directors of then publicly held company zygo corporation from  through  dr banucci was first elected a director of cognex in  he currently serves as lead director on the board of clean harbors inc a publicly held company listed on the new york stock exchange he holds a ba in chemistry from beloit college and a phd in organic chemistry from wayne state university theodor krantz vice president and chief financial officer airmar technology corporationmr krantz has been vice president and chief financial officer of airmar technology corporation a world leader in ultrasonic sensors for the marine and industrial markets since may   he was president of airmar technology inc from  until taking on his current role from  to  he served as president and later chief executive officer of velcro industries mr krantz was first elected a director of cognex in   he also serves as a director and member of the audit committees of hitchiner manufacturing company and control air inc  mr krantz holds a ba from princeton university and an mba from harvard university jeffrey miller former president markem corporationmr miller is the former president of markem corporation a leading global provider of product identification solutions and traceability solutions where he spent a year career  in  he managed the sale of the company to dover corporation and retired from the company in   he has served on numerous nonprofit boards local government agencies and commissions and devotes significant time in an advisory and board capacity to nonprofit organizations mr miller was first elected a director of cognex in  he also serves as a member of the board of directors of two private companies  mr miller holds an ab from dartmouth college and an mba from harvard university bruce robinson former chairman and ceo zygo corporationmr robinson is the former chairman and ceo of then publicly held company zygo corporation a worldwide supplier of optical metrology instruments precision optics and electrooptical design and manufacturing services he joined zygo in   retired from the company in  and served as consultant from  to  prior to that mr robinson served as president of worldwide operations for the foxboro company a  billion manufacturer of instruments and control systems for process industries he began his year career at the foxboro company as a systems engineer in  mr robinson was elected a director of cognex in  he holds a bsc in electrical engineering from the university of waterloo in canada jerry schneider business consultantmr schneider has been an independent business and financial consultant since  from  to  he was the chief financial officer of vistage international a private equityowned ceo peeradvisory membership company with over  members prior to vistage mr schneider spent seven years at fresenius medical care—north america a global dialysis service and products company where he served as chief financial officer and later as senior vice president of strategic planning between  and  mr schneider was the executive vice president and chief financial officer of then publicly held grancare inc gc a healthcare company in the longterm care assisted living and institutional pharmacy business mr schneider was first elected a director of cognex in  he serves on a number of other forprofit and nonprofit boards mr schneider received his juris doctor from loyola law school and a bs in accounting from the university of california at berkeley he is an inactive cpa and attorney in the state of california anthony sun former managing general partner venrock associatesmr sun was the managing general partner and chief executive officer of venrock associates a venture capital partnership from  until his retirement in  he joined venrock in  and was a general partner of venrock from  until  mr sun was first elected a director of cognex in  he also serves as a member of the board of directors of several private companies robert j willett president and chief executive officer mr willett has been chief executive officer of cognex since march   he joined cognex in june  as the president of the modular vision systems division mvsd and was promoted to president and chief operating officer in january   mr willett came to cognex from danaher corporation a diversified manufacturer of industrial controls and technologies where he served as vice president of business development and innovation for the company’s product identification business group  prior to that mr willett was president of videojet technologies a leader in coding and marking products which is a subsidiary of danaher he was first elected a director of cognex in  mr willett holds a ba from brown university and an mba from yale university   products to meet all your needs vision sensors vision systems d laser profilers fixedmount readers handheld readers mobile terminals barcode verifiers   learn more cognex video library knowledge base training customer stories white papers ondemand webinars upcoming webinars useful tools interactive games   about us investor relations cognex jobs leadership team in the news environment giving   contact us get a demo contact sales get product pricing technical support work for cognex we are growing and are looking for the best talent worldwide   connect with us facebook linkedin cognex tv twitter partner tv google   technical downloads partner login investors privacy change country   cognex corporation j bruce robinson appointed chief executive officer about us company profile news releases trade show schedule manufacturing locations salesservice offices how to get to zygo patent information iso registrations conflict minerals policy code of business conduct and ethics news release november   j bruce robinson appointed chief executive officer middlefield connecticut november  zygo corporation nasdaqzigo today announced that j bruce robinson president has been appointed chief executive officer mr robinson succeeds gary k willis who remains with the company as chairman of zygos board of directors mr robinson joined zygo as its president and chief operating officer in january of this year gary willis who served as ceo since  said this appointment continues the management succession process begun earlier this year bruce has very ably directed the company through this calendar year as we have experienced three quarters of sequential order revenue and profit growth he has earned the confidence this appointment signifies bruce robinson commenting on his appointment stated i appreciate the opportunity the board has given me and am most enthusiastic about the companys future prospects you can count on my best efforts to appropriately reward our shareowners zygo corporation designs develops manufactures and markets high performance measurement and yield improvement instruments systems and accessories used in high technology industries the company is headquartered in middlefield connecticut and also has operations in asslar germany longmont colorado and in newbury park sunnyvale and simi valley california this press release may contain forwardlooking statements within the meaning of section a of the securities act of  as amended and section e of the securities exchange act of  as amended which reflect the companys current judgment on certain issues because such statements apply to future events they are subject to risks and uncertainties that could cause the actual results to differ materially important factors which could cause actual results to differ materially are described in the companys reports on form k and q on file with the securities and exchange commission features ›› zygo corporation introduces verifire™ hdx laser interferometer with ultrahighresolution and imaging for precise d metrology of optical components and systems ›› two zygo scientists are recipients of the  rudolf kingslake medal and prize ›› zygo corporation partners with adcole corporation on d surface metrology system for advanced process control of automotive powertrain component manufacturing ›› zygo corporation introduces miniature optical position sensor for highprecision motion sensing and positioning applications ›› article coating high quality custom optics risk reduction through supplier evaluation ›› zygo corporation enhances industryleading verifire™ laser interferometers for improved performance and value ›› upcoming trade shows laser germany semicon west m